CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Consumer Protection – Retail Transactions for Essential Consumer Goods –
3 Cash Payments
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a merchant, in a certain transaction between certain hours,
5 from prohibiting a person from making a cash payment to purchase a an essential
6 consumer good or service, requiring a person to purchase a an essential consumer
7 good or service by using a credit or debit card, or charging or collecting from a person
8 a fee higher price than for an equivalent cashless transaction for making a cash
9 payment for the purchase of a an essential consumer good or service, subject to
10 certain exceptions; establishing that a violation of this Act is an unfair, abusive, or
11 deceptive trade practice subject to certain enforcement and penalty provisions under
12 the Maryland Consumer Protection Act; and generally relating to retail cash
13 transactions for essential consumer goods.
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
